Analysis of the organic medical substances and the theoretical basis are learned. Students learn synthesis, molecular properties of organic medical substances and methods for qualitative and quantitative analysis. Structure-activity relationship in selected groups of medical substances is introduced.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of pharmaceutical chemistry course is to introduce pharmacy students to the organic medical substances focusing on properties and methods of qualitative and quantitative analysis.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  The student that graduated the course: -	is familiar to organic medical substances introduced during course -	based on the molecular properties is able to choose valid methods for qualitative and quantitative analysis of medical substances -	can describe structure-activity relationships in selected groups of medical substances.
